Hello hectorespert,

you are right - even an empty zip / jar file must not been empty.
In the Java packages   java.util.zip   and   java.util.jar   there is no
"createNew...File" method.

You must define your own method.   Here is my solution for setup:

void setUp(){
      ....................
      createNewJarFile(getDataDir(), "JavaApplication1.jar");  

@SuppressWarnings("UseSpecificCatch")
    public void createNewJarFile(File dir, String jarName){
        String path = dir.getPath()+File.separator+jarName;             
      
        File jarFile = new File(path);
        ZipOutputStream os;
        try {
            os = new ZipOutputStream(new FileOutputStream(jarFile));
            os.close();
         }catch(Exception ex){
            assertNull(ex.getMessage());
        }
   }

Happy coding,

Rik

